Python package is just a system directory hierachy structure to organise files.

To create a package for a few modules
package
  mod1.py
  mod2.py

or
package
  package-sub1
    mod1.py
    mod2.py

Import module in a package
```
from package import mod1
```
Import function from package module
```
import package.mod1
from package.mod1 import functionName
```

Import all from a package

The following won't load any modules in it
```
import package
```

Add __init__.py initialization to the package, so that python will automatically load all modules in that folder
package
  __init__.py
  mod1.py
  mod2.py
__init__.py will be executed 

import * and __all__
from module import * will import all objects defined in the module
from package import * will import all modules defined in __all__ dictionary
```
__all__ = [
        'mod1',
        'mod2',
        'mod3',
        'mod4'
        ]
```
